tracks/nmv03pprlbb.name: tracks/nmv03pprlbb
tracks/nmv03pprlbb.description:
my entry!
-
pretty much the whole idea is pretty much said in the title, this is a very heavy inspired song from the early 2000s Game NFS, they brought some of the best trance, techno mix songs I've heard. I was constantly surrounded by reggae music in Puerto Rico when this game was released, hearing Ekstraks Theme songs just blew my mind, opened my ears to a new world of sound I was never familiar with, plus, I love cars! This game did a big number on me when it came to music and cars. Just wanted to give a massive tribute to it by making my own theme inspired by this same game. I hope you guys like it as much as I am. Also, let me know how close I was to recreating that feeling!
-
If you're ever driving and hear this song all of the sudden, I'm right behind you

tracks/apfn3p7evg8w.name: tracks/apfn3p7evg8w
tracks/apfn3p7evg8w.description:
people who make diary/warheart @noah_cheng @choukradziad93_gmail_com @JJTHEKING etc.,
[Diary (sub-genre of Pluggnb)]
_____________________________
(remix is on for help)
diary is a type of genre that is heavily focused on the mixture of insp. anime ost melodies (Your Lie in April osts for example), with pluggnb influenced drums. Diary differs but in is somewhat similar from pluggnb because the melodies and sounds are further more complex than the average plugg track, IMO.

HOW TO MAKE DIARY/WARHEART
00:00
first, ya wanna start out w/ some very calm, sad-toned chords that sound like sad anime chords
I would recommend Heisenberg for the main chords
00:14
add a high-pitched string that fairly complements the main chord mel (it up 2 u)
I would recommend Space for this one.
00:27
Add an INSANE main lead to make the song pop out (boring lead = boring song). Put your main lead in legato mode and make sure your lead has an exciter on it so it won't drown out into the song
00:41
OPTIONAL: Add a groovy background mel that also complements (I prefer the background melodies to be in triplets, but it is up 2 u)
You can use any synthesiser idk

the drums are easy, if you know trap drum placement on the machiniste, and are good at mixing drums, you are good lol.

tracks/uc878q6o9.name: tracks/uc878q6o9
tracks/uc878q6o9.description:
Definitely one of my best instrumental songs ever. I turned towards experimental with the chiptune, and it just went everywhere.

I think though that this song means a lot to me, and I hope that it means a lot to YOU. because I made this song, not for those who wanna listen, like, reply on it, but for the veterans; the veterans that everybody forgot, and just thought of it as a day of the calender. Just remember, these veterans died, suffered, and fought for our freedom. So when you listen to this song, thank the veterans of the US Military, not me.

Thanks for everyone who has supported me the whole way through, and all the veterans that fought so I could have a safe life through out my life.
